rComments: Robert David is very very knowledgable and still works in his field which means lots of good examples/stories/case studies. Lectures can still sometimes be boring but other times he shows videos etc. Assignments are clear and rather interesting. I'll actually use what I learned in his class after I graduate. Solid choice for a prof.

He is very passionate about his field and wants his students to succeed. He likes to show TED Talks and videos in class which I enjoyed. Sometimes he goes on rants that aren't related to the course material but I still found it very interesting (entertaining). His assignments were fair and he was not a tough grader.

Robert is a good professor. His lectures are fairly interesting and he likes to share really cute lifestyle advice with his students. He is particular with his grading, so make sure you follow the instructions closely. I found the topics of the papers a bit difficult. Sometimes he repeats himself. I would take a class with him again.

Robert David, is pretty corky. His lectures are boring but it is an easy class, he goes off topic a lot but that's because he has a lot of experience. He is very kind and nice. He also brings in a lot of guest speakers that work in the field to give us hope in finding a job after we graduate.

He is a really great prof, he is really passionate about international development but he tends to go off topic a lot and talk about very specific examples of past experiences. Although interesting, it can become long. All together really enjoyed the class.

His lectures are very dry, although he tries to bring in guest lecturers and videos which make the class a little more interesting. All evaluations are take home "exams", which are usually 15-20 page papers that you can usually do in groups. Material covered in class isn't relevant for these take homes. Takes attendance. Very easy marker. EN and FR
Great professor His stories make the course material come alive. Take a class with him if you get the chance
Really Funny, helpful, and has a lot of practical experience. Makes learning in the summer not the end of the world and walks you through assignments

This was an excellent prof! His teaching was really hands-on and rejected just focusing on theory. He also has a lot of actual development experience and shares it with the class. Awesome class, awesome prof!
